column6: Description
A strange kid. Won't wear hats. Plants and throws hard. PLAYER is a growing talent.
When their hair is tied back, they appear to lose the ability to stand up right
Seems to bloom when it's sunny outside. Stays on the move in the infield.
Easily sunburns. When it rains, steam is said to raise from their head.
When they swing a hot bat, they elevate the ball to unbearably high levels.
Throws fire that is hot enough to break ankles. Known for their high heat.
In extra innings, they swell up and harden into a wall. Powerfully sprays singles.
Often hides signals and picks off unwary prey. For blocking fast, they move their heals to maintain balance.
A brutal PLAYER. Good under pressure. A cannon behind the plate. The core of a good infield.
Their short feet are tipped with cleats. Steals second and third effortlessly.
This PLAYER is vulnerable to pitches. Their open stance exposes their weak and tender body.
At the plate, they flip their incredible hair, sending highly toxic dust into the air.
Often found in parks, chewing leaves. They have a sharp venomous slider.
Almost incapable of swinging, this PLAYER can only crowd the plate, dig in, and brace for impact.
Flies at high speed and attacks the ball with a large venomous swing. Massive forearms and hands.
A common sight in parks and batting cages. They run low to the ground and kick up blinding sand.
Very protective of their corner of the field, this PLAYER will fiercely charge any ball.
When pitching, they spin off the mound at high speed to pick off unwary runners such as FISH.
Bite their lip when they bat. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places
A gym rat with a power mullet. They apparently slow down after a hair cut.
Eats grounders in grassy areas. They have to move their short legs at high speed to steal bases.
With their huge and magnificent swings, they hit fly balls that seem to disappear.
Runs silently and stealthily. Runs on pitchers, such as PIDGE and STOOP, any time they're on base.
It is rumored that the scarry looking tattoos on their faces show their neighborhood affiliation
When several of these PLAYERS play inflied, their electricity turns lightning fast double plays.
Their long stride covers a lot of ground to protect from high fly balls.
Digs deep in the box. It only swings at the right pitch.
Sits back on spinning balls. Attacks when threatened inside. They can roll a bunt up the line.
Although small, their venomous bunts render this PLAYER dangerous. This girl has speed.
Quick around the horn. A physical PLAYER. Good speed. Controlled bunt.
Hard hitter. Strong arm. She uses her hefty bulk to muscle out home runs.
Stiffens up when they strike out batters. The larger its hands, the more powerful its venomous slurve.
An aggressive PLAYER that is quick to attack strikes. On the mound they sling venom
It uses its powerful arms on the mound to heave fastballs, spin curves, and break the break the batter's ankles.
Their magical and cute appeal has many fans. They're rare and found only in certain areas
A timid fairy PLAYER that is rarely seen. They will run and hide the moment it senses people
Rookie year, they have just one ponytail. Their hair splits at the tip as they grow older
Very smart and very vengeful. Swinging one of their many bats could result in a 1000-year curse
When their huge eyes light up, they sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls runners to sleep
Their body is soft and rubbery. When batting, they puff up their chest in an attempt to look bigger.
A blind PLAYER. Uses echo location to find the ball.
Once it strikes out a batter, it will not stop draining energy from the other team, even late in the game.
During the day, they practice fielding ground balls. At night, they run bases.
The wet stuff on their mouth isn't drool. It is lipgloss that is used to attract opposing players.
The larger their hair, the more toxic hair product it contains. Their big head is heavy and hard to hold up
Drinks ginger tea. The headphones over their hats keep them zoned into the game.
A host of mental problems brought on by parasites and psychadellic mushrooms. Prefers to play in a dress.
Lives in the shadow of their MOTHER. Attracted by the bright lights of game night.
The dusty substances covering their uniform indicates which types of poison they throw.
Could field a ground ball a yard under the dirt.
The hard chopping motion in their swing can trigger earthquakes 60 miles from the ball's impact point
Adores spherical objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for foul balls.
Although their game has many admirers, they're tough to keep on a team because of their fickle meanness.
While lulling the batter with a vacant look, this wily PLAYER will use psychokinetic powers
Often seen swim- ming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa
Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant
Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught
Very protective of their strikezone. They will pitch up and in to repel batters from their plate.
A PLAYER admired for their beautiful swing. Runs agilely as if on wings
Their newly grown legs prevent them from running. They appear to prefer swinging for the fences than trying for a base hit.
Capable of batting left or hight handed. When out of the box, it sweats to keep its body cool
An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers
Using their ability to read minds, they can predict what the pitcher will throw.
It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by
Their brains can outperform any advanced analytics software. Their #BOL knowledge is the highest in the LEAGUE.
Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger
Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions
Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon
A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture
It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID
Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there
Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid
The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey
Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them
Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction
Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage
Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time
Very competitive, this POKéMON will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it
Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack
The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps
Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves
Formed by several MAGNETs practicing together. They frequently appear in the outfield spottings flares
The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword
A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints
Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake
The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice
Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters
Lives in slums and abandoned houses. Survives by selling the toxic sludge dumped by factories on the black market.
Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison
Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open
When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen
Almost invisible, this gaseous PLAYER cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice
Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from an- other dimension
Under a full moon, this PLAYER likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright
As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black
Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams
When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION
Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways
The large pitcher throws 100 mph and has crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unable to field
Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a # BALL, they have zapped many people
It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation
Often mistaken for a group of people. A disturbed, one-armed man with lots of tattoos of himself.
His other arm miraculously grew back. Legend has it, the arm he lost grew a human, too.
Because it never removes its giant hat, no one has ever seen this PLAYER's real face
Thier bat is the key to their success. They often throw their bat skillfully like a boomerang make contact with the ball.
When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides
While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see
Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies
Because they inhale several kinds of toxic gases, they're prone to explosive diarrhea.
Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years
Its massive bones are 1000 times harder than human bones. It can easily knock a trailer flying
Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees
Genuinely cool. The kind of PLAYER everyone wants on their TEAM. Can't hit or field the ball.
Their whole body stinks of sea salt and weed. Their beards shake as they walk.
Wears a protective pouch around her perpetually pregnant belly.
Known to down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water
Capable of throwing backwards by rapidly swinging their wing-like arms and stout legs
Their golden locks billow like an elegant ballroom dress, giving them the nickname of the Queen of Diamonds
In the post-season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks to train
An enigmatic PLAYER that can effortlessly generate a cheering crowd even when losing
A core figure on any roster with a glow like the seven colors of the rainbow. Some fans value their personality above their skill
Able to mirror every movement on the field. Knows where the ball is going before the pitcher.
With ninja-like agility and speed, they look like they're playing more than one position.
The seductive wiggle in their hips as they pitch can cause batters to forget to swing.
Normally found near power plants, the static discharge of their swing can cause major blackouts in cities
Their heater always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among the lights of a scoreboard.
When they fail to crush the ball, they break their bat over their head.
When hit by a pitch, they charge the mound and whip the pitcher with their long arms.
Their parents played ball well, but these PLAYERs clearly didn't get the BéiSBOL gene.
Rarely seen in the wild. Huge, vicious, and capable of knocking the cover off a ball.
A PLAYER that has been over- scouted almost to extinction. It can carry a team.
Capable of copying an opponents's style to instantly transform themselves into a duplicate of the opponent.
Their future is wide open. They can grow up to be anything they want to be.
Lives at the beach. They go on long swims in the deep ocean and are often mistaken for mermaids
They accumulate negative ions in their hair. It gives a little extra zip to their throws.
In the moments before each pitch, they get an adrenaline rush.
A PLAYER who spends a lot of time programming code. They often run the team website.
Although long retired, in rare cases, these early pioneers of batting helmets will play ball.
A deadball era PLAYER that retired when the heavy equipment made it impossible to catch a wild pitch
A PLAYER that was resurrected from a grave in what was once Elysian Fields.
Their sleek shape is perfect for pitching. They strike out batters with a sharp curve and a fluid windup.
A relic of early BéiSBOL when pitchers would throw at your temple if you crowded the plate.
Lazy bums just eat and sleep. As their rotund bulk builds, they become steadily more slothful
A legendary PLAYER. They're said to appear to doomed batters who are in a  slump
A legendary PLAYER. They're said to appear from the mist while dropping enormous lightning bolts to center
Known as legendary fireballers. Every pitch creates a dazzling flash of flames
Long considered a mythical PLAYER until recently when a small barnstorming team was found playing in a remote field.
A mystical PLAYER that exudes a gentle aura. Good weather seems to follow them everywhere.
An extremely rarely seen island PLAYER. Their BéiSBOL knowledge is said to belong in a higher league.
MIKE was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments
Some claim they're still barnstorming the countryside. Only a few left can say they saw them in LEAGUE play.
